{
  "stem": "2353.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we would open the door and throw all the drapes and everything that nobody would find out that, that somebody was in the house who didn't belong there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it, it, it was a terrible time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, you can't imagine the-- what the-- what the Nazis could think up to do next to you.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Jewish families weren't allowed to have non-Jewish maids, for instance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Or, if there was a maid, you had to be afraid that she would hear something, and would denounce you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My little brother who was-- he was what-- was about six at the time, when he started to go to school, the best friends next door to him, they would start to beat him up and spit at him.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, they were-- they were all brainwashed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The children would brainwash the ch-- the parents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The parents would brainwash the children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this poor little kid who was six years old didn't know why.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why was this happening?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These children were his playmates for six years, and all of the sudden they would beat him up and call him terrible names.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I would walk him to school as often as I could.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I couldn't dare to touch these children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I would-- you know, they would call me all kinds of wild names.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They would spit at me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I couldn't dare to touch them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it wasn't--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I always say the Holocaust means to American people mostly what happened in the concentration camps, but very few people know how degraded we felt after having been accepted so fully.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, in that town where I lived, my uncle was on the city council, and everybody was-- the Jewish people were all respected and mixing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was just no, no separation whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
